"Data Scientist – Lead
Vancouver Remote– Open to Canadian remote candidates
Information Technology
Excellent Salary and attractive benefits

Our Canadian based SaaS Marketing client, is seeking a Senior Data Scientist create and build and lead exciting projects in data science, and machine learning. This position heads a small Data focused team while still having the ability to dive into new techniques in deep learning, reinforcement learning, NLP and find creative ways to deliver value to our customers with machine learning and data backed insights.


The Role:
Manage, and mentor a team of Data Scientists and Machine Learning Engineers
Collaborate with a larger team of Data Scientists, Machine Learning Engineers, Developers, Analysts, Product Managers, and UX Designers
Drive machine learning research into a variety of areas focused on empowering our customers to create high converting content, optimize their ad campaigns, and provide data driven insights to increase their ROI
Learn and be challenged with machine learning areas, such as cutting-edge NLP utilizing attention based and generative models, image analysis, and reinforcement learning
Strategize and build the Data Products, vision, and planning
The Ideal Candidate:
5 or more years of experience working with machine learning and data science
Experience leading major projects and managing junior team members
Experience with one or more deep learning technologies and frameworks (NLP, image analysis, generative models)
Programming with Python and the associated data science/machine learning packages (e.g. scikit-learn, pandas, xgboost, numpy, scipy, pytorch, or tensorflow)
Relational databases (we principally use MySQL and Postgres)
Agile development, version control, and code review processes
You can communicate clearly and empathetically with developers, product managers, and UX designers to explain the abilities and limitations of ML systems"
